{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed model consists of two parts: discriminative and generative attention modeling (DGAM).",
    "On one hand, discriminative attention modeling trains a classification model on temporally pooled features weighted by the frame attention.",
    "On the other hand, a generative model, i.e., a variational conditional auto-encoder (VAE), is learned to model the class-agnostic frame-wise distribution of representation conditioned on attention values.",
    "By maximizing the likelihood of the representation, the frame-wise attention is optimized accordingly, leading to good separation of action and context frames.",
    "As shown in Fig. 48, the model is divided into two alternating stages, (a) and (b), for training."
  ]
}